quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  40,69,Have you not seen towards those who dispute against Ayaatillahe how are they being turned away (from the Message)
  40,70,"Those who have belied Al-Kitab and that with what We sent therewith Our Messengers, soon they will come to know (their fate). [Certain ordainments in Al-Kitab, like Itikaf, Salat, Tawaf, Umra, Hajj and Zakat adopt a practical format when being implemented. The format adhered to by all the Prophets of Allah is the only format recognised by Him. It is preserved by Him at and around Kaba. See Verse No 2/125, 17/77-79 and]"
  40,71,"When (there are) iron-collars in their necks, and (they stand hand-cuffed and fettered in) chains, they shall be dragged (along) —"
  40,72,"in the boiling water, then in the Fire they will be thrown"
  40,73,"then it is said to them: “Where are those whom you used to join as partners —"
  40,74,"besides Allah?” They said: “They have vanished from us. Nay, we did not use to invoke any thing in previous (world).” Thus Allah allows the disbelievers to lose the track"
  40,75,"This is to you because of what you used to enjoy in the earth without right, and because you used to rejoice insolently"
  40,76,Enter the gates of Hell becoming abiders therein. So (what an) evil abode for the arrogants
  40,77,"So be patient, the promise of Allah is true. So if whatever We may show you — some of what We promise them, or We cause you to die, then to Us they shall be returned back"
  40,78,"And indeed, We have sent Messengers before you; out of them is that whom We have narrated unto you, and of them is that whom We did not narrate unto you. And it was not (suitable) for a Messenger that he may approach with a credential — except under permission of Allah. So when the decree of Allah proceeded, the decision was taken in full justice, and then and there lost those who indulged in falsehood and forgery"